#include 'template.wml'

<points>


<li>
Usually just marking text will copy it to the clipboard.
</li>

<li>
Sometimes however, you'll have to press <tt>Ctrl+C</tt> or the menus'
copy command to copy the marked text to the clipboard.
</li>

<li>
Pressing the middle mouse button will paste it to the active
window. (if you don't have a middle button - you can press the left
and right mouse buttons together to paste).
</li>

</points>
